The paper deals with communication complexity, which is a central topic in theoretical computer science and falls under the category of cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also discusses the implications of the lower bound on data stream computations, which suggests a connection to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of information theory in the paper suggests a possible connection to cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the use of space lower bounds, which suggests a connection to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
